dc_description_s: These data layers represent zoning boundaries for Langlade County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase Langlade_Zoning_2018.gdb. The feature layers included in this geodatabase are NFarmPresDATCPN, NFP_OverlayN, and NZoningN.[FarmPresDATCP: This layer represents farmland preservation areas in Langlade County, Wisconsin referenced to the Wisconsin Transverse Mercator System (WTM) GCS_North_American_1983_HARN.FP_Overlay: Layer created for Langlade County's Farmland Preservation Zoning Ordinance Update.Zoning: Original Zoning Boundaries for Langlade County, WI were derived from older paper maps updated at least annually by the Zoning Office. One of the first digital layers which are the source of todayâ€™s Zoning Layer Map was completed October 28, 2013 by the North Central Regional Planning Commission. That digital layer is a compilation of those older records, information and data and is intended for reference purposes only. An important note is the Zoning Map was completed first by hand and then digitally a number of years prior to a full Parcel digital map was in place in December 2017. An ongoing effort to align the zoning maps to the parcels is being made.]
dct_provenance_s: Arthur H. Robinson Map Library - University of Wisconsin
